3 Rail Picture Frame Fence

The 3 rail picture frame adds a third horizontal rail and matching trim for extra rigidity and a distinctive craftsman profile. Built in #1 grade cedar and planned with Fence Genius, it delivers a premium, long‑lasting privacy fence.

Craftsman Look
Added Structure
Fence Genius Precision
Popular Upgrade to Picture Frame
Homeowners choose the 3 rail variant for added strength and a refined, architectural finish.

Why homeowners choose 3 rail picture frame

  • Extra rail increases panel rigidity and durability over time.
  • Third trim board mirrors the rail layout for a balanced craftsman aesthetic.
  • Cedar construction excels in the Pacific Northwest climate.
  • Fence Genius planning delivers precise grade-following panels and clean top lines.

How we build 3 rail picture frame (our standard)

  • Three 2x4 rails, screwed directly into the posts.
  • Trim that frames each panel with an added third trim to complement the third rail.
  • Top 2x4 cap for a finished profile.
  • Standard posts: 4.125" x 4.125" x 9' set approximately 2' deep with ~180 lbs of properly mixed concrete.
  • Stainless steel fasteners standard to prevent corrosion and black streaking.

Fence Genius planning for 3 rail designs

  • Set new posts first to establish a stable baseline.
  • Capture post-to-post measurements, usable post height, grade change, and angles.
  • Panels are optimized to follow the ground at both top and bottom for a clean, consistent look.

3 Rail Picture Frame FAQs

Is this stronger than standard picture frame?

Yes, the added rail improves rigidity and helps long runs stay straighter over time.

Can I combine with board‑on‑board or rot board?

Absolutely. These upgrades pair nicely with the 3 rail layout and enhance privacy and durability.
